COMMANDS:

load:
	load FileLocationToLoad FileNameToSave
	
	Loads image from file path FileLocationToLoad and saves it to FileNameToSave.
	Multiple images can be loaded at once. No other commands will work without 
	loading an image first. Supports .ppm .jpg .png
	
save:
	save FileLocationToSave FileNameToSave
	
	Saves a given image FileNameToSave to file path FileLocationToSave. Extension of filepath
	determines filetype. Supports .ppm .jpg .png
	
brighten:
	brighten FileNameToEdit FileNameToSave BrightenValue
	
	Brightens a given image FileNameToEdit by BrightenValue and saves it to FileNameToSave. 
	BrightenValue can be negative and MUST be an integer. Will clamp values to maximum/minimum 
	pixel brightness (generally 0-255).

red-component:
	red-component FileNameToEdit FileNameToSave
	
	Greyscales a given image FileNameToEdit and saves it to FileNameToSave. Greyscale based on 
	the red RGB values of each pixel.
	
green-component:
	green-component FileNameToEdit FileNameToSave
	
	Greyscales a given image FileNameToEdit and saves it to FileNameToSave. Greyscale based on 
	the green RGB values of each pixel.
	
blue-component:
	blue-component FileNameToEdit FileNameToSave
	
	Greyscales a given image FileNameToEdit and saves it to FileNameToSave. Greyscale based on 
	the blue RGB values of each pixel.
	
value-component:
	value-component FileNameToEdit FileNameToSave
	
	Greyscales a given image FileNameToEdit and saves it to FileNameToSave. Greyscale based on 
	the value of each pixel.
	
intensity-component:
	intensity-component FileNameToEdit FileNameToSave
	
	Greyscales a given image FileNameToEdit and saves it to FileNameToSave. Greyscale based on 
	the intensity of each pixel.
	
luma-component:
	luma-component FileNameToEdit FileNameToSave
	
	Greyscales a given image FileNameToEdit and saves it to FileNameToSave. Greyscale based on 
	the luma of each pixel.
	
horizontal-flip:
	horizontal-flip FileNameToEdit FileNameToSave
	
	Horizontally flips a given image FileNameToEdit and saves it to FileNameToSave.
	
vertical-flip:
	vertical-flip FileNameToEdit FileNameToSave
	
	Vertically flips a given image FileNameToEdit and saves it to FileNameToSave.
	
sepia:
	sepia FileNameToEdit FileNameToSave
	
	Color transforms a given image FileNameToEdit using sepia and saves it to FileNameToSave.
	
greyscale:
	greyscale FileNameToEdit FileNameToSave
	
	Color transforms a given image FileNameToEdit using a greyscale transform and saves it to FileNameToSave.
	
blur:
	blur FileNameToEdit FileNameToSave
	
	Blurs a given image FileNameToEdit and saves it to FileNameToSave.
	
sharpen:
	sharpen FileNameToEdit FileNameToSave
	
	Sharpens a given image FileNameToEdit and saves it to FileNameToSave.